              </p>

              <h2>FAQ about Alberta income tax</h2>

              <h3>Is Alberta still a low‑tax province?</h3>
              <p>
                Alberta has no provincial sales tax (PST) and only charges the
                5% federal GST on most purchases, which keeps overall tax
                burdens relatively low. However, its personal income tax
                advantage has narrowed compared with some other provinces as
                rates and brackets have changed over time.
              </p>

              <h3>How often are tax brackets updated?</h3>
              <p>
